WEBVTT

00:00.735 --> 00:03.702
<i>[haunting music]</i>

00:03.738 --> 00:06.305
[police sirens wailing]

00:06.340 --> 00:07.706
¶ ¶

00:07.742 --> 00:10.709
- Here's to our first dinner
in our new house.

00:10.745 --> 00:13.812
- It was in a pretty bad area.

00:13.848 --> 00:16.415
- You girls be sure
and lock your door at night.

00:16.450 --> 00:17.583
- We had no other options.

00:17.618 --> 00:18.717
- [breathing heavily]

00:18.753 --> 00:19.718
¶ ¶

00:19.754 --> 00:21.086
<i>[glass shatters]</i>

00:21.122 --> 00:23.255
- Kristin, Lindsay, get in here!

00:23.290 --> 00:24.256
- Something's not right.

00:24.291 --> 00:26.025
- [screaming]

00:26.060 --> 00:28.060
- It's okay, it's okay,
it's okay, it's okay.

00:28.095 --> 00:29.962
- Kristin's covered in blood.

00:29.997 --> 00:32.264
- Kristin!
Oh, my God, what's happening?

00:32.299 --> 00:33.766
- She's just screaming
her head off.

00:33.801 --> 00:35.567
<i>- I'm really scared.</i>
<i>I don't know what to do.</i>

00:35.603 --> 00:37.269
<i>- You need to get out</i>
<i>of the house right now.</i>

00:37.304 --> 00:39.171
- [screaming]
Stop!

00:39.206 --> 00:40.672
- I thought I was gonna die.

00:40.708 --> 00:43.208
[evil shrieking]

00:43.244 --> 00:46.178
<i>[haunting music]</i>

00:48.983 --> 00:51.917
<i>[woman humming]</i>

00:55.423 --> 00:58.390
<i>[mellow guitar music]</i>

00:58.426 --> 01:06.365
¶ ¶

01:12.273 --> 01:15.174
<i>- I was in my senior year</i>
<i>of college.</i>

01:15.209 --> 01:17.142
¶ ¶

01:17.178 --> 01:18.877
<i>I was an animation major.</i>

01:18.913 --> 01:20.579
¶ ¶

01:20.614 --> 01:22.748
Everything that I'd been doing
for the last four years

01:22.783 --> 01:26.752
had been leading up to this,
my graduation.

01:26.787 --> 01:28.754
[phone chiming]

01:28.789 --> 01:30.622
¶ ¶

01:30.658 --> 01:31.857
<i>- Hey, Kristin!</i>

01:31.892 --> 01:33.425
- Hey!

01:33.461 --> 01:36.128
- Me and Lindsay bonded with
each other almost instantly.

01:36.163 --> 01:37.596
- Mwah, mwah, mwah, mwah.

01:37.631 --> 01:39.465
- Kristin is a loyal friend.

01:39.500 --> 01:42.034
She will do anything for you.

01:42.069 --> 01:43.435
- Look who I just ran into.

01:43.471 --> 01:44.636
- Who?

01:44.672 --> 01:47.506
¶ ¶

01:47.541 --> 01:48.740
Lindsay?

01:49.910 --> 01:51.276
Aah!

01:51.312 --> 01:52.544
Jerk.

01:52.580 --> 01:54.313
- We're always playing tricks
on each other.

01:54.348 --> 01:55.380
- I totally got you.

01:55.416 --> 01:56.381
<i>- We're always laughing.</i>

01:56.417 --> 01:57.616
We're always joking around.

01:57.651 --> 01:59.785
[phone chiming]

01:59.820 --> 02:01.453
- Hey, Stacie.

02:01.489 --> 02:03.856
I see you found
a new actor for your film.

02:03.891 --> 02:06.758
- Stacie is a very quiet person.

02:06.794 --> 02:08.160
- Hi.

02:08.195 --> 02:10.496
- They're both loud
and they complement each other,

02:10.531 --> 02:12.698
and I'm kind of the quiet
one of the group.

02:12.733 --> 02:14.967
<i>- So how's the house</i>
<i>hunting going, guys?</i>

02:15.002 --> 02:16.602
- I've got one more left.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.070
We just arrived.
Do you want to see it?

02:18.105 --> 02:19.371
- Our biggest problems
are the fact

02:19.406 --> 02:20.706
that we didn't have
a place to stay

02:20.741 --> 02:22.274
<i>before the new quarter started.</i>

02:22.309 --> 02:24.109
So we really needed
to find a place

02:24.145 --> 02:25.611
and we needed to find it quick.

02:25.646 --> 02:29.481
<i>[spooky music]</i>

02:29.517 --> 02:32.551
- It was in a pretty bad area.

02:32.586 --> 02:34.153
[police siren whooping]

02:34.188 --> 02:35.754
<i>There were some drug issues.</i>

02:35.789 --> 02:37.356
It had a little bit
of a reputation.

02:37.391 --> 02:39.658
- Come on, term's
in a couple of weeks.

02:39.693 --> 02:41.994
Let's at least look inside.

02:44.131 --> 02:45.831
- We had no other options.

02:48.135 --> 02:50.002
¶ ¶

02:50.037 --> 02:51.103
- [gasps]

02:51.138 --> 02:52.137
¶ ¶

02:52.173 --> 02:54.473
- Ooh.
- What do you think?

02:54.508 --> 02:56.875
- It was literally everything
we were looking for.

02:56.911 --> 02:59.011
<i>It had the three bedrooms,</i>
<i>the two baths.</i>

02:59.046 --> 03:00.145
- It's pretty big.

03:00.181 --> 03:01.980
- It was awesome.

03:02.016 --> 03:02.981
- [shrieking]

03:03.017 --> 03:03.949
- Aah!

03:06.053 --> 03:08.921
- I got you good, girl!

03:08.956 --> 03:10.455
- Don't do that.

03:10.491 --> 03:11.924
- The house was just
what we needed.

03:11.959 --> 03:14.126
- You like it? She likes it.

03:14.161 --> 03:19.097
¶ ¶

03:24.905 --> 03:27.973
<i>- A week later,</i>
<i>we moved into the house.</i>

03:28.008 --> 03:29.808
My father helped us move down.

03:29.843 --> 03:31.243
- I can take that.
- Okay.

03:31.278 --> 03:32.377
- Thanks.

03:32.413 --> 03:35.414
- Having Kristin attend college
in Savannah

03:35.449 --> 03:39.618
is very far from our hometown
in New York.

03:39.653 --> 03:43.889
<i>I had some concerns because</i>
<i>it was a rougher area of town,</i>

03:43.924 --> 03:47.893
but her brother Kyle
was only five minutes away

03:47.928 --> 03:49.428
in case anything
ever happened.

03:49.463 --> 03:51.363
- Thanks.
- Hey, Kyle.

03:51.398 --> 03:53.465
Promise me you'll look
after your sister, okay?

03:53.500 --> 03:54.933
- Yeah.
- Okay.

03:54.969 --> 03:56.902
- Yeah, I'm not
gonna be far away.

03:56.937 --> 03:58.937
And you're fine, right?

03:58.973 --> 04:00.839
- Dad, don't worry.

04:00.874 --> 04:01.840
- You're sure?

04:01.875 --> 04:03.609
- It's only for a year.

04:03.644 --> 04:05.377
I graduate soon,
and then I'll be out of here.

04:05.412 --> 04:06.411
- At the end of the day,

04:06.447 --> 04:07.913
she was going
to the best college

04:07.948 --> 04:10.015
for animation, and that's what
she really wanted.

04:10.050 --> 04:11.016
- Okay.

04:11.051 --> 04:12.684
<i>[spooky piano music]</i>

04:12.720 --> 04:14.353
Take care, okay?
And call me if you need me.

04:14.388 --> 04:15.354
- Okay.

04:15.389 --> 04:23.328
¶ ¶

04:29.136 --> 04:32.070
<i>[distant arguing]</i>

04:39.313 --> 04:41.913
- We lived
in a very noisy neighborhood.

04:41.949 --> 04:44.716
<i>It was a lot of people</i>
<i>walking around.</i>

04:44.752 --> 04:45.717
A lot of cat-calling.

04:45.753 --> 04:47.819
[whistling]

04:47.855 --> 04:49.254
-<i> Hey!</i>

04:49.290 --> 04:52.157
- Here's to our first dinner
in our new house.

04:54.928 --> 04:57.229
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

04:57.264 --> 04:59.064
-<i> What?</i>
<i>- Get out of my face, boy!</i>

04:59.099 --> 05:00.365
- The first night we moved in...

05:00.401 --> 05:02.334
<i>[gunshots firing]</i>

05:04.004 --> 05:05.737
There were gunshots.

05:05.773 --> 05:07.939
¶ ¶

05:07.975 --> 05:10.242
[knocking at door]

05:10.277 --> 05:13.111
We ended up getting
a knock at our door.

05:13.147 --> 05:21.086
¶ ¶

05:32.433 --> 05:33.632
- Hmm.

05:33.667 --> 05:35.400
Thought I could see lights.

05:35.436 --> 05:36.935
Ya'll supposed to be here?

05:36.970 --> 05:38.270
- She was immediately
on top of us.

05:38.305 --> 05:40.138
- We're students
from the college.

05:40.174 --> 05:42.174
We just moved in.

05:42.209 --> 05:44.343
- College girls, huh?

05:44.378 --> 05:47.179
You can call me Mama,
everybody else does.

05:47.214 --> 05:48.180
- Hi, Mama.
- Hey, Mama.

05:48.215 --> 05:49.281
- Hi.

05:49.316 --> 05:50.615
- We've been having
some problems

05:50.651 --> 05:53.151
in the last few years
with this place.

05:53.187 --> 05:55.854
- Mama said that at night
there had been squatters

05:55.889 --> 05:58.990
and homeless people coming in
and out and living there.

05:59.026 --> 06:01.526
- You girls be sure
and lock your door at night.

06:01.562 --> 06:03.995
- That's not really what
somebody wants to hear

06:04.031 --> 06:05.797
when they first move
into a house.

06:05.833 --> 06:06.798
- Thanks.

06:06.834 --> 06:11.970
¶ ¶

06:12.005 --> 06:14.940
[car alarm blaring]

06:22.649 --> 06:25.584
[pipes creaking]

06:27.187 --> 06:28.420
- [sighs]

06:29.490 --> 06:31.423
[Skype sounding]

06:33.694 --> 06:34.826
<i>- Hi.</i>

06:34.862 --> 06:36.128
- Ladies.

06:36.163 --> 06:37.262
<i>It's coffee time.</i>

06:37.297 --> 06:39.264
<i>all: Rock, paper, scissors.</i>

06:39.299 --> 06:41.333
[laughter]

06:41.368 --> 06:42.934
<i>- Fine.</i>
<i>- See you, loser.</i>

07:10.230 --> 07:15.267
¶ ¶

07:15.302 --> 07:18.804
- I see the chair on top
of the dining room table.

07:20.808 --> 07:22.607
I kind of thought
that maybe Kristin or Lindsay

07:22.643 --> 07:25.410
were pulling a prank on me
or just trying to mess with me.

07:25.446 --> 07:27.379
[roaring and banging]

07:29.450 --> 07:31.283
- Stacie?

07:31.318 --> 07:32.417
What the heck was that?

07:32.453 --> 07:34.619
- You tell me.
- It wasn't me.

07:34.655 --> 07:36.655
- It obviously wasn't me.

07:36.690 --> 07:39.658
- We're all just kind of staring
at each other going,

07:39.693 --> 07:42.027
"Okay, well, one of us
must have done it."

07:42.062 --> 07:43.995
- Suit yourselves.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.130
¶ ¶

07:45.165 --> 07:46.665
-<i> Stacie got more upset</i>

07:46.700 --> 07:49.968
'cause she thought
she was the butt of the joke.

07:50.003 --> 07:51.536
[door slams]

07:54.475 --> 07:57.442
[crickets chirping]

07:57.478 --> 08:04.549
¶ ¶

08:04.585 --> 08:07.085
- One evening,
we were working in our rooms.

08:07.120 --> 08:09.154
¶ ¶

08:09.189 --> 08:11.723
<i>I was working</i>
<i>on my senior film.</i>

08:11.758 --> 08:14.693
<i>I had a few shots</i>
<i>to catch up on.</i>

08:14.728 --> 08:17.562
I was a little bit behind.

08:17.598 --> 08:20.999
- Animation is very intense.

08:21.034 --> 08:24.903
There is 10 hours of work
in one second of good animation.

08:24.938 --> 08:27.105
We were pretty much
in the house all the time.

08:27.140 --> 08:28.473
¶ ¶

08:28.509 --> 08:30.442
- I was working on my computer

08:30.477 --> 08:33.812
and I was trying to get
this work done before Monday.

08:33.847 --> 08:36.515
<i>[garbled audio]</i>

08:42.022 --> 08:48.727
¶ ¶

08:54.935 --> 08:57.869
<i>[audio flickers]</i>

09:00.774 --> 09:01.706
All of a sudden...

09:02.876 --> 09:04.242
The power just cuts out.

09:04.278 --> 09:05.544
- Aargh!
- You guys?

09:05.579 --> 09:06.878
- Is this happening to you too?

09:06.914 --> 09:09.014
Oh, my God.

09:09.049 --> 09:10.682
<i>- Our deadline</i>
<i>was in a few days,</i>

09:10.717 --> 09:12.417
and I'd lost about
two hours of work.

09:12.452 --> 09:13.885
¶ ¶

09:13.921 --> 09:17.689
I found a few candles
'cause I don't like the dark.

09:17.724 --> 09:25.664
¶ ¶

09:42.916 --> 09:45.383
I didn't want
to be in there alone.

09:45.419 --> 09:46.751
- Girls?

09:46.787 --> 09:49.321
Lindsay? Kristin?

09:52.693 --> 10:00.632
¶ ¶

10:04.204 --> 10:05.170
Linds?

10:05.205 --> 10:13.144
¶ ¶

10:18.952 --> 10:21.086
Hey, wait for me.

10:21.121 --> 10:29.060
¶ ¶

10:40.741 --> 10:42.207
Linds?

10:44.044 --> 10:45.010
Aah!

10:45.045 --> 10:51.549
¶ ¶

10:51.585 --> 10:53.118
There you are.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.787
<i>- We decided to go out</i>
<i>onto the street and figure out</i>

10:55.822 --> 10:57.088
why we lost power.

10:57.124 --> 11:00.492
¶ ¶

11:00.527 --> 11:02.627
- Maybe we blew a fuse
or something.

11:02.663 --> 11:10.602
¶ ¶

11:16.576 --> 11:18.009
- We found our power box.

11:18.045 --> 11:19.844
- Can someone shine a light?

11:19.880 --> 11:20.979
- Yeah.

11:22.649 --> 11:24.582
[metal creaking]

11:24.618 --> 11:32.557
¶ ¶

11:35.228 --> 11:36.594
- Nothing happened.

11:38.832 --> 11:39.931
- So what now?

11:41.001 --> 11:42.000
- Wait until light I guess?

11:42.035 --> 11:43.435
[metal banging]

11:46.673 --> 11:47.639
- Okay.

11:47.674 --> 11:55.613
¶ ¶

11:57.150 --> 12:00.752
- I remembered that my laptop
was fully charged

12:00.787 --> 12:02.187
<i>and instead of sitting</i>
<i>in the dark</i>

12:02.222 --> 12:03.922
<i>we could be listening to music.</i>

12:03.957 --> 12:05.824
<i>So I decided to go</i>
<i>into my room and get it.</i>

12:05.859 --> 12:10.195
¶ ¶

12:10.230 --> 12:12.363
<i>When I get a few feet</i>
<i>from my door,</i>

12:12.399 --> 12:13.598
something's not right.

12:13.633 --> 12:15.967
I don't see any lights
coming from my room.

12:16.002 --> 12:21.573
¶ ¶

12:21.608 --> 12:24.109
Every single candle
was blown out.

12:24.144 --> 12:26.111
<i>There was no reason</i>
<i>for them to be out.</i>

12:26.146 --> 12:28.146
The window wasn't open.

12:28.181 --> 12:29.748
¶ ¶

12:29.783 --> 12:32.150
And then I saw
something really weird.

12:32.185 --> 12:33.251
¶ ¶

12:33.286 --> 12:34.753
<i>Every single one</i>
<i>of my figurines</i>

12:34.788 --> 12:37.088
<i>was turned around</i>
<i>and facing the wall.</i>

12:37.124 --> 12:39.324
- Kristin, Lindsay, get in here!

12:39.359 --> 12:40.325
- Who was in our house?

12:40.360 --> 12:43.294
¶ ¶

12:48.134 --> 12:50.735
[distant siren blaring]

12:50.770 --> 12:53.104
- Kristin, Lindsay, get in here!

12:59.479 --> 13:00.911
Come on guys, this isn't funny.

13:00.947 --> 13:02.880
- I'm like, "What's not funny?
What's going on?"

13:02.915 --> 13:04.482
- Look at my collection.

13:06.786 --> 13:11.822
¶ ¶

13:11.858 --> 13:13.524
- It was very creepy.

13:13.559 --> 13:15.693
It was very, just, unnerving.

13:15.728 --> 13:17.261
¶ ¶

13:17.296 --> 13:19.296
- My first instinct
was they're pranking me.

13:19.332 --> 13:20.664
They're trying
to make me scared.

13:20.700 --> 13:22.366
- Come on, it's got to be you.

13:22.402 --> 13:23.768
- No.

13:23.803 --> 13:25.936
We were with each other
the whole time.

13:25.972 --> 13:27.671
¶ ¶

13:27.707 --> 13:29.640
- Oh, no.
- What?

13:29.675 --> 13:31.642
- I started to think maybe
while we were outside

13:31.677 --> 13:34.045
that someone
had snuck into our house.

13:34.080 --> 13:38.783
¶ ¶

13:38.818 --> 13:40.184
- We had to search the house.

13:40.219 --> 13:47.158
¶ ¶

13:48.494 --> 13:51.295
I wanted to go through
every possible place

13:51.330 --> 13:52.329
that anybody could hide.

13:52.365 --> 13:55.733
¶ ¶

13:55.768 --> 13:58.536
- We checked in the bathroom.

13:58.571 --> 14:00.071
- We searched the laundry room.

14:00.106 --> 14:08.045
¶ ¶

14:17.557 --> 14:20.091
- Every shadow seems
to be a person.

14:20.126 --> 14:27.298
¶ ¶

14:27.333 --> 14:28.532
<i>And then--</i>

14:28.568 --> 14:30.334
bam!

14:30.369 --> 14:31.735
The lights came back on.

14:31.771 --> 14:34.805
¶ ¶

14:34.841 --> 14:36.307
There was nothing there.

14:36.342 --> 14:37.308
- [sighs]

14:37.343 --> 14:40.444
¶ ¶

14:40.480 --> 14:42.146
- [laughs]

14:42.181 --> 14:43.981
¶ ¶

14:44.016 --> 14:46.417
- Let's get out of here.
- Yeah.

14:46.452 --> 14:48.285
¶ ¶

14:48.321 --> 14:49.753
- We were always
a little bit cautious

14:49.789 --> 14:51.055
in the house after that.

14:57.029 --> 15:03.334
¶ ¶

15:03.369 --> 15:04.902
<i>It was around midterms,</i>

15:04.937 --> 15:08.239
<i>and we're constantly</i>
<i>pushing ourselves.</i>

15:08.274 --> 15:11.842
We probably pulled about
three all-nighters a week.

15:11.878 --> 15:14.979
<i>- We were more worried about</i>
<i>our work than anything else.</i>

15:15.014 --> 15:17.047
The pressure was really immense.

15:17.083 --> 15:18.916
¶ ¶

15:18.951 --> 15:20.818
<i>- We had a deadline coming up.</i>

15:22.288 --> 15:24.088
I felt trapped in that house.

15:26.225 --> 15:27.992
<i>- Hey, Kristin, how you doing?</i>

15:28.027 --> 15:29.260
- Hey, I'm good, Dad.

15:29.295 --> 15:30.694
<i>- And what about your brother?</i>

15:30.730 --> 15:32.630
<i>Does he--does he come by</i>
<i>and visit every so often?</i>

15:32.665 --> 15:34.899
- Yes, yeah he comes by
to check up on me.

15:34.934 --> 15:37.168
¶ ¶

15:37.203 --> 15:38.802
Don't worry.

15:38.838 --> 15:45.142
¶ ¶

15:45.178 --> 15:47.645
[thumping]

15:47.680 --> 15:49.246
- All of a sudden,
I just started hearing,

15:49.282 --> 15:52.716
like, a thump noise.
Like a pounding sound.

15:52.752 --> 15:54.084
<i>- What's going on?</i>

15:54.120 --> 15:55.085
- Dad?

15:55.121 --> 15:56.086
<i>- Hello? Kristin?</i>

15:56.122 --> 15:58.923
- Dad? You're breaking up.

15:58.958 --> 16:00.624
[thumping]

16:00.660 --> 16:03.460
- Lindsay!

16:03.496 --> 16:05.596
Lindsay, cut it out will you?

16:05.631 --> 16:06.897
- Sorry!

16:11.470 --> 16:17.942
¶ ¶

16:17.977 --> 16:20.945
<i>[spooky music]</i>

16:20.980 --> 16:23.647
[thumping]

16:23.683 --> 16:26.083
<i>- Then I start hearing</i>
<i>the thump noise again.</i>

16:26.118 --> 16:29.053
[thumping]

16:41.200 --> 16:43.300
I immediately thought
it's Lindsay.

16:43.336 --> 16:45.202
- Lindsay, knock it off.

16:45.238 --> 16:47.037
It's too late to be doing that!

16:48.374 --> 16:50.774
- All right, what is that?

16:50.810 --> 16:52.843
¶ ¶

16:52.878 --> 16:55.813
[crickets chirping]

16:56.916 --> 16:58.949
¶ ¶

16:58.985 --> 17:02.453
<i>That night,</i>
<i>I was settling into bed.</i>

17:02.488 --> 17:06.223
<i>And it takes me quite some time</i>
<i>to get to sleep.</i>

17:06.259 --> 17:08.559
<i>My mind tends to wander.</i>

17:08.594 --> 17:11.929
¶ ¶

17:11.964 --> 17:13.130
<i>Finally,</i>

17:13.165 --> 17:14.865
I fall into a deep sleep.

17:16.769 --> 17:19.003
[woman humming]

17:20.539 --> 17:22.806
I suddenly wake up.

17:22.842 --> 17:25.542
<i>And I'm looking around</i>
<i>thinking why am I awake?</i>

17:25.578 --> 17:27.278
¶ ¶

17:27.313 --> 17:29.246
I look around.

17:33.386 --> 17:35.019
¶ ¶

17:35.054 --> 17:36.520
And there's this woman.

17:38.457 --> 17:39.657
She's staring at me.

17:42.194 --> 17:43.861
I blink.

17:45.031 --> 17:46.764
And then she's gone.

17:46.799 --> 17:53.270
¶ ¶

17:53.306 --> 17:54.805
What did I just see?

17:56.676 --> 17:58.275
Maybe it's the stress of school.

17:59.345 --> 18:01.178
<i>Maybe it was just a dream.</i>

18:03.249 --> 18:07.084
¶ ¶

18:07.119 --> 18:10.254
Spring Break came,
and I was just so excited

18:10.289 --> 18:12.323
to go home.

18:12.358 --> 18:14.692
<i>- Both me and Lindsay lived</i>
<i>in North Carolina,</i>

18:14.727 --> 18:16.560
so it's not that long
of a drive.

18:18.497 --> 18:21.498
- I was ready to be out
of Savannah at this point.

18:21.534 --> 18:22.800
- Okay.

18:22.835 --> 18:25.736
<i>- I was happy to get away</i>
<i>from that house.</i>

18:25.771 --> 18:27.037
- Love you.
- Love you too.

18:27.073 --> 18:28.305
- I'll see you soon.

18:28.341 --> 18:29.673
¶ ¶

18:29.709 --> 18:31.742
<i>- Living in New York, and going</i>
<i>to school in Georgia--</i>

18:31.777 --> 18:33.744
<i>it's such a long trip.</i>

18:33.779 --> 18:37.514
There was no way I could even
take the time to go home.

18:37.550 --> 18:38.482
[horn honks]

18:42.421 --> 18:44.254
<i>[eerie breathing]</i>

18:44.290 --> 18:49.226
¶ ¶

18:50.629 --> 18:56.667
¶ ¶

18:56.702 --> 18:57.735
<i>When the girls left,</i>

18:57.770 --> 18:59.236
I was feeling
a little bit unnerved.

18:59.271 --> 19:01.405
¶ ¶

19:01.440 --> 19:03.874
I really didn't want
to be in the house alone.

19:03.909 --> 19:08.912
¶ ¶

19:14.553 --> 19:16.086
<i>Later that day,</i>

19:16.122 --> 19:18.288
I was sitting
in my room reading a book.

19:22.628 --> 19:25.362
[thumping]

19:25.398 --> 19:27.531
All of a sudden,
I start hearing banging.

19:27.566 --> 19:29.867
[thumping]

19:29.902 --> 19:33.637
When Lindsay jogs in her room,
the whole house shakes.

19:33.672 --> 19:36.473
<i>But there was no one else</i>
<i>in the house with me.</i>

19:36.509 --> 19:39.443
[thumping continues]

19:45.017 --> 19:47.451
It's coming
from Lindsay's bathroom.

19:47.486 --> 19:53.056
¶ ¶

19:53.092 --> 19:56.427
It just stops immediately.

19:56.462 --> 19:57.428
[glass shatters]

19:57.463 --> 19:58.996
- Where the hell
have you been all night?

19:59.031 --> 20:00.531
- At work.
I work all day!

20:00.566 --> 20:02.800
<i>- It wasn't that weird for us</i>
<i>to hear random noises</i>

20:02.835 --> 20:04.001
echoing through the house...

20:04.036 --> 20:05.369
[indistinct arguing]

20:05.404 --> 20:08.005
<i>But the window is open again.</i>

20:12.478 --> 20:19.450
¶ ¶

20:19.485 --> 20:21.418
[police siren whooping]

20:23.122 --> 20:25.422
[indistinct radio chatter]

20:29.128 --> 20:31.929
- At this point, I'm spending
more and more time in my room.

20:36.669 --> 20:39.603
[dog barking]

20:45.277 --> 20:47.344
[phone vibrating]

20:47.379 --> 20:48.445
<i>It's a text from Lindsay...</i>

20:48.481 --> 20:50.113
[phone vibrating]

20:50.149 --> 20:52.382
Saying that she needed me
to go in her room

20:52.418 --> 20:54.251
and find a notebook for her.

20:54.286 --> 20:55.486
[police siren whoops]

20:55.521 --> 20:59.857
[phone chimes]

21:06.265 --> 21:07.831
- [screaming]

21:07.867 --> 21:08.932
- My heart just stops.

21:08.968 --> 21:09.933
- [screaming]

21:09.969 --> 21:12.903
¶ ¶

21:18.411 --> 21:21.346
<i>[distant sirens blaring]</i>

21:26.653 --> 21:29.554
- [screaming]

21:29.589 --> 21:30.855
- When I look again--

21:32.926 --> 21:36.494
it's just Lindsay's
graduation gown...

21:36.530 --> 21:37.829
hanging from the ceiling.

21:37.864 --> 21:40.431
¶ ¶

21:40.467 --> 21:41.900
I was so angry with Lindsay.

21:41.935 --> 21:44.969
I thought she was
messing with me.

21:45.005 --> 21:46.371
She knew I was alone
in the house.

21:46.406 --> 21:48.506
[phone vibrating]

21:48.542 --> 21:49.874
<i>- My phone buzzed,</i>

21:49.910 --> 21:52.343
<i>and it's a picture message</i>
<i>from Kristin.</i>

21:52.379 --> 21:56.447
She's like, "Why in the hell
did you put your graduation gown

21:56.483 --> 21:57.849
on your ceiling?"

21:57.884 --> 22:01.686
<i>I told Kristin, "That's weird.</i>
<i>I did not do that.</i>

22:01.721 --> 22:04.055
I put it in my closet."

22:04.090 --> 22:05.056
¶ ¶

22:05.091 --> 22:06.157
-<i> Lindsay's my best friend.</i>

22:06.193 --> 22:07.692
She's telling me
she didn't hang it up,

22:07.727 --> 22:09.694
but I'm looking right at it.

22:09.729 --> 22:11.396
<i>It was freaking me out.</i>

22:11.431 --> 22:17.368
¶ ¶

22:20.307 --> 22:23.274
[woman humming]

22:23.310 --> 22:26.644
¶ ¶

22:26.680 --> 22:30.014
<i>I started to wish that</i>
<i>I had gone home at that point.</i>

22:30.050 --> 22:31.983
[police siren wailing]

22:34.120 --> 22:38.756
I was so...trapped.

22:38.792 --> 22:43.695
¶ ¶

22:43.730 --> 22:46.664
[phone vibrating]

22:48.435 --> 22:49.434
- Hey, sweetie, what's up?

22:49.469 --> 22:50.702
<i>- Hey, Dad.</i>

22:50.737 --> 22:53.738
- Kristin called me and told me
that some strange things

22:53.773 --> 22:55.640
were happening around the house.

22:55.675 --> 22:56.674
- Right.

22:56.710 --> 22:58.309
- Lindsay swears
that she didn't do it,

22:58.345 --> 23:00.745
so I don't know how
it got there.

23:00.780 --> 23:02.380
<i>- Hmm.</i>

23:02.415 --> 23:05.516
<i>- I wondered if there was</i>
<i>somebody playing jokes on them.</i>

23:05.552 --> 23:07.752
Maybe not the girls, but maybe--

23:07.787 --> 23:10.121
the house had a history
of vagrancy.

23:10.156 --> 23:13.358
- Make sure all the doors
and windows are locked, okay?

23:13.393 --> 23:15.393
- I was starting
to get concerned.

23:15.428 --> 23:16.861
<i>- I'm sure it's nothing.</i>

23:16.897 --> 23:18.630
<i>It's just...</i>

23:18.665 --> 23:19.764
¶ ¶

23:19.799 --> 23:21.766
I don't know, lonely here.

23:22.969 --> 23:24.269
<i>- I told Kristin</i>

23:24.304 --> 23:26.771
I was coming to Atlanta
on a business trip,

23:26.806 --> 23:28.373
and when it was over,
I wanted to come down

23:28.408 --> 23:29.774
and spend a couple of days
with her.

23:29.809 --> 23:32.210
- I'll only be a few hours away
if you need me, okay?

23:32.245 --> 23:35.980
- Okay, thanks, Dad. Bye.

23:44.691 --> 23:46.624
<i>[creepy music]</i>

23:48.528 --> 23:51.462
[crickets chirping]

23:54.334 --> 23:56.801
<i>[upbeat music playing]</i>

23:56.836 --> 23:59.437
<i>- At this point, I'm spending</i>
<i>more and more time in my room.</i>

24:01.007 --> 24:04.943
I literally only leave it
for bathroom breaks,

24:04.978 --> 24:06.678
<i>and that's only during</i>
<i>daylight.</i>

24:06.713 --> 24:08.513
I don't leave
after it gets dark.

24:08.548 --> 24:10.481
[computer mouse clicking]

24:12.786 --> 24:14.719
[woman humming]

24:15.956 --> 24:19.490
And I start hearing
this weird singing.

24:19.526 --> 24:22.460
[humming continues]

24:28.568 --> 24:31.002
I'm thinking that it's coming
from the neighbor's house.

24:31.037 --> 24:38.977
¶ ¶

24:46.553 --> 24:48.886
I start to realize
that it's actually coming

24:48.922 --> 24:50.555
from inside the house.

24:50.590 --> 24:52.623
¶ ¶

24:52.659 --> 24:55.626
[humming continues]

24:55.662 --> 24:58.563
It sounds like it's coming
from Stacie's room.

25:03.803 --> 25:07.839
¶ ¶

25:07.874 --> 25:10.208
<i>I'm starting to panic.</i>

25:10.243 --> 25:12.076
I need to get out of the house.

25:12.112 --> 25:15.747
¶ ¶

25:19.185 --> 25:23.154
But I'm afraid of leaving
the house in the dark.

25:32.766 --> 25:33.998
I call Lindsay immediately.

25:34.034 --> 25:35.333
[Skype sounding]

25:35.368 --> 25:37.301
- Hey, what's up, girl?

25:37.337 --> 25:40.938
<i>- Lindsay, there's someone</i>
<i>in the house singing, humming.</i>

25:40.974 --> 25:42.940
- She sounded
obviously panicked.

25:42.976 --> 25:45.043
- Wait, what?
Humming? Slow down.

25:46.646 --> 25:47.979
- Lindsay, I know
it sounds crazy,

25:48.014 --> 25:51.115
but I need you to listen to it.

25:51.151 --> 25:54.018
- So I take the phone
and I hold it against the wall.

25:54.054 --> 25:56.521
<i>[woman humming]</i>

25:56.556 --> 25:57.855
<i>- Do you hear it?</i>

26:00.927 --> 26:04.228
- There is someone in this house
singing, humming.

26:06.566 --> 26:09.100
And I just feel so creeped out.

26:09.135 --> 26:10.468
<i>- Lindsay, I'm really scared.</i>

26:10.503 --> 26:11.702
<i>I don't know what to do.</i>

26:11.738 --> 26:14.138
- It's okay, just, okay,
just call your dad okay?

26:14.174 --> 26:16.074
- He's gonna know what to do.

26:16.109 --> 26:17.508
<i>- Okay, I'm gonna call him.</i>

26:17.544 --> 26:19.243
¶ ¶

26:19.279 --> 26:22.213
[phone vibrating]

26:24.984 --> 26:25.950
- Kris?

26:25.985 --> 26:26.951
<i>- Dad?</i>

26:26.986 --> 26:28.920
- Kristin called me
in a real panic.

26:28.955 --> 26:31.456
She was terrified of what
was happening in the house.

26:31.491 --> 26:33.057
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa--
- There's someone's singing.

26:33.093 --> 26:34.492
- Slow down, slow down.
What's going on?

26:34.527 --> 26:36.360
- She told me, "There's
singing in the room next to me."

26:36.396 --> 26:38.196
- Just listen to it.

26:38.231 --> 26:39.163
[woman humming]

26:41.167 --> 26:43.968
<i>- It raised the hair</i>
<i>on the back of my neck.</i>

26:44.003 --> 26:46.437
My first concern was--
is there someone in the house?

26:46.473 --> 26:47.605
- Make sure you lock your door.

26:47.640 --> 26:49.273
I'm calling your brother
right now, okay?

26:49.309 --> 26:50.274
<i>- Okay.</i>

26:50.310 --> 26:51.409
- All right, then.

26:51.444 --> 26:53.377
[humming continues]

26:54.881 --> 26:55.847
- Yeah, I'm here.

26:55.882 --> 26:57.048
<i>- My dad called,</i>

26:57.083 --> 26:58.716
telling me, you know,
"You need to get over

26:58.751 --> 26:59.684
to Kristin's house."

27:00.887 --> 27:02.620
Kristin?

27:02.655 --> 27:03.588
- Hi.

27:06.693 --> 27:09.260
<i>- Kyle immediately</i>
<i>came in and said</i>

27:09.295 --> 27:11.996
he wanted to confront
whatever was happening.

27:15.969 --> 27:18.136
- I'm like, okay, wow,
there's some crazy lady

27:18.171 --> 27:20.638
that I'm gonna have
to get rid of.

27:20.673 --> 27:24.208
¶ ¶

27:24.244 --> 27:27.178
[humming grows louder]

27:35.822 --> 27:38.389
The door knob, it was ice cold.

27:39.826 --> 27:40.758
<i>I'm freaking out.</i>

27:42.395 --> 27:45.329
¶ ¶

27:50.336 --> 27:58.275
¶ ¶

28:01.013 --> 28:02.680
[woman humming]

28:02.715 --> 28:04.648
- As soon as it clicks...

28:07.653 --> 28:08.886
The singing stops.

28:19.131 --> 28:20.831
And nothing there.

28:20.866 --> 28:23.601
No one's there,
no one's in the room.

28:23.636 --> 28:25.536
- There's nothing here.

28:25.571 --> 28:27.638
- I never believed in,
like, ghosts, or paranormal,

28:27.673 --> 28:29.540
or anything like that.

28:30.676 --> 28:34.144
But, you know, this--
this is weird.

28:34.180 --> 28:38.482
¶ ¶

28:38.517 --> 28:40.284
- Look, are you sure
you don't want to just stay

28:40.319 --> 28:41.318
at my place tonight?

28:41.354 --> 28:43.087
- I had to finish
my senior film,

28:43.122 --> 28:46.090
and I had so much work to do.

28:46.125 --> 28:47.491
- Yeah.

28:47.526 --> 28:49.393
- I didn't have a choice.

28:51.764 --> 28:53.597
I really wanted to speak
to my dad again.

28:53.633 --> 28:56.100
- Right, well, I'll--
I'm heading for Savannah

28:56.135 --> 28:58.435
first thing
in the morning, okay?

28:58.471 --> 29:00.170
All right, sweetheart.

29:07.513 --> 29:08.479
<i>[mellow rock music]</i>

29:08.514 --> 29:11.582
<i>- ¶ I know, I know ¶</i>

29:11.617 --> 29:13.417
<i>- So I went to the new</i>
<i>burritos place</i>

29:13.452 --> 29:15.019
<i>that opened down the street.</i>

29:15.054 --> 29:18.188
<i>Oh, my God, it was so good.</i>

29:18.224 --> 29:20.457
<i>Next time you come and visit,</i>
<i>I have to take you there.</i>

29:20.493 --> 29:22.192
<i>It was amazing.</i>
<i>You're gonna die.</i>

29:22.228 --> 29:24.561
- When we're not together,
we like to FaceTime.

29:24.597 --> 29:26.363
- You know, it's so nice
to just be talking

29:26.399 --> 29:28.299
about any old junk again.

29:28.334 --> 29:29.833
- Gee, thanks a lot.

29:29.869 --> 29:34.505
- No, I mean to not have
to think about animation, or.

29:36.309 --> 29:38.042
- It makes me feel like there's
someone else in the house.

29:38.077 --> 29:39.476
Makes me feel
a little bit less uncomfortable

29:39.512 --> 29:41.011
with everything
that's been going on.

29:41.047 --> 29:42.212
<i>[doorbell rings]</i>

29:42.248 --> 29:44.214
<i>- Hang on, I think</i>
<i>I just heard the door.</i>

29:44.250 --> 29:46.216
<i>Don't go anywhere. BRB.</i>

29:46.252 --> 29:49.353
<i>- Right, where am I gonna go?</i>

29:49.388 --> 29:57.328
¶ ¶

30:08.674 --> 30:11.642
<i>[eerie pulsating music]</i>

30:11.677 --> 30:19.616
¶ ¶

30:35.701 --> 30:37.835
<i>- Just one second!</i>

30:41.307 --> 30:43.340
<i>Sorry that took so long.</i>

30:43.376 --> 30:45.676
<i>Wait, what's that?</i>

30:45.711 --> 30:46.777
- What?

30:46.812 --> 30:49.380
- She goes, "Kristin,"
my door's open.

30:49.415 --> 30:50.681
<i>- Did you go in there?</i>

30:52.451 --> 30:55.986
- And she looks behind her
and she looks back at me.

30:56.021 --> 30:57.721
- Are you trying
to freak me out?

30:57.757 --> 30:59.123
<i>- No, I swear.</i>

30:59.158 --> 31:00.858
<i>Can you go check it out?</i>

31:00.893 --> 31:02.192
- No way.

31:02.228 --> 31:03.527
- She goes,
"It's still daylight.

31:03.562 --> 31:04.828
It's fine. You'll be fine.

31:04.864 --> 31:05.829
Go in there."

31:05.865 --> 31:08.499
- I'll stay online with you.

31:08.534 --> 31:10.234
<i>- Fine.</i>

31:15.408 --> 31:18.108
- I walk down
the hallway with Lindsay.

31:18.144 --> 31:26.083
¶ ¶

31:30.990 --> 31:32.856
- Lindsay!

31:32.892 --> 31:34.291
- What? What is it?

31:39.198 --> 31:42.332
- My room is destroyed.

31:42.368 --> 31:44.201
- You need to get out
of the house right now.

31:44.236 --> 31:45.702
<i>Get out of the house right now.</i>

31:45.738 --> 31:48.405
¶ ¶

31:48.441 --> 31:50.140
- [screams]

31:50.176 --> 31:51.508
- What's wrong?

31:53.179 --> 31:55.012
<i>- When my dad showed up</i>
<i>at the house,</i>

31:55.047 --> 31:59.683
I was so relieved knowing that
he was gonna be staying with me.

31:59.718 --> 32:03.754
<i>- I went through every room,</i>
<i>every closet.</i>

32:03.789 --> 32:06.824
I wanted to know for sure that
there was no one in this house.

32:06.859 --> 32:09.793
[crickets chirping]

32:13.999 --> 32:16.967
That night, I slept on the floor
in Kristin's bedroom.

32:17.002 --> 32:24.942
¶ ¶

32:36.622 --> 32:38.288
- That was the first
full night's sleep I got

32:38.324 --> 32:40.757
in the entire week I was alone.

32:40.793 --> 32:43.727
[humming]

32:46.899 --> 32:49.833
[humming continues]

33:00.913 --> 33:02.279
<i>- When I woke up,</i>

33:02.314 --> 33:04.548
knowing that there was nothing
that happened that night,

33:04.583 --> 33:06.450
I guess there was a little doubt
in my head that...

33:08.120 --> 33:11.054
Maybe my daughter
was under a lot of stress.

33:17.763 --> 33:21.632
When I finished my shower
and I opened the curtain...

33:21.667 --> 33:24.468
¶ ¶

33:24.503 --> 33:25.802
- All of a sudden, I hear--

33:25.838 --> 33:28.071
- Kristin? Kristin!

33:28.107 --> 33:29.439
- Dad?

33:29.475 --> 33:30.941
- Kristin, get in here.

33:30.976 --> 33:32.276
- Dad?

33:32.311 --> 33:34.344
¶ ¶

33:34.380 --> 33:36.146
Dad?

33:37.750 --> 33:39.783
<i>- Written in the steam</i>
<i>on the mirror</i>

33:39.818 --> 33:42.452
was "they are mine."

33:42.488 --> 33:45.422
¶ ¶

33:50.362 --> 33:53.797
¶ ¶

33:53.832 --> 33:56.299
- Kristin? Kristin!

33:56.335 --> 33:57.601
- Dad?

33:57.636 --> 33:58.868
- Kristin, get in here!

33:58.904 --> 34:00.437
- Dad?

34:07.879 --> 34:09.713
I don't want to see this.

34:11.149 --> 34:13.550
- Who are you?

34:13.585 --> 34:15.919
What do you want?

34:15.954 --> 34:17.988
- Now I'm having
experiences at the house.

34:18.023 --> 34:19.956
And now I'm getting a warning?

34:19.992 --> 34:21.491
A warning from what?

34:21.526 --> 34:23.460
¶ ¶

34:27.132 --> 34:30.500
<i>- We got back to Savannah</i>
<i>as fast as we could.</i>

34:30.535 --> 34:31.968
My best friend is there,

34:32.004 --> 34:37.707
and I wouldn't want to be stuck
in this situation by myself.

34:37.743 --> 34:39.609
- As much as I didn't want
to leave,

34:39.645 --> 34:42.112
I had to get back to New York.

34:42.147 --> 34:46.283
<i>She was pretty adamant</i>
<i>about staying in the house.</i>

34:46.318 --> 34:47.450
¶ ¶

34:47.486 --> 34:50.587
- Graduation, for me,
was everything.

34:52.891 --> 34:54.824
I had to stay.

34:57.529 --> 35:00.230
- Hey, guys, check this out.

35:00.265 --> 35:04.200
Only 33 days before we graduate.

35:04.236 --> 35:10.674
¶ ¶

35:10.709 --> 35:13.843
- We're ready to graduate
and we're ready to leave.

35:13.879 --> 35:18.481
¶ ¶

35:18.517 --> 35:21.618
<i>- We had started packing</i>
<i>months before we had to move</i>

35:21.653 --> 35:24.087
because we just wanted
to be out of there.

35:24.122 --> 35:25.689
¶ ¶

35:34.266 --> 35:35.732
[rustling]

35:38.103 --> 35:41.037
¶ ¶

35:52.584 --> 35:55.218
- Oh, I didn't see
you there, Stace.

35:55.253 --> 35:58.388
It's amazing how much stuff you
can accumulate in a year, huh?

35:59.825 --> 36:01.491
What are you looking
for in there?

36:02.928 --> 36:04.127
Stacie?

36:07.399 --> 36:09.566
¶ ¶

36:09.601 --> 36:12.001
- I--I thought I was looking
at evil.

36:12.037 --> 36:12.969
¶ ¶

36:15.006 --> 36:16.740
[glass shatters]

36:16.775 --> 36:19.075
- [screaming]

36:19.111 --> 36:20.310
- Kristin?

36:20.345 --> 36:21.811
¶ ¶

36:21.847 --> 36:23.113
- Hey, what's wrong?

36:23.148 --> 36:25.582
- Kristin?
- Hey, hey, shh.

36:25.617 --> 36:28.051
- There was a woman
on the couch.

36:28.086 --> 36:29.052
¶ ¶

36:29.087 --> 36:31.788
[sniffling and sobbing]

36:31.823 --> 36:33.423
- This is when I started
to believe

36:33.458 --> 36:35.392
that there was something
in the house

36:35.427 --> 36:37.026
<i>that we just couldn't explain.</i>

36:39.264 --> 36:41.498
¶ ¶

36:41.533 --> 36:42.499
- Ready?

36:42.534 --> 36:44.501
<i>- After Kristin saw that woman,</i>

36:44.536 --> 36:46.770
we decided that no one
should be allowed to stay

36:46.805 --> 36:49.672
in that house by themselves,
especially at night.

36:49.708 --> 36:52.108
- Hey, college girls!

36:52.144 --> 36:54.244
Doing all right?

36:54.279 --> 36:56.980
You don't look all right.

36:57.015 --> 37:00.450
- Uh, yeah, we were just
working late, that's all.

37:00.485 --> 37:02.786
- Everything okay in there?

37:02.821 --> 37:04.154
- Um...

37:04.189 --> 37:06.956
- We asked Mama if anything
had happened in the house.

37:06.992 --> 37:09.192
- Hey, you mentioned squatters.

37:09.227 --> 37:10.794
I was wondering if any history

37:10.829 --> 37:13.029
in the house
we should know about?

37:13.064 --> 37:15.732
- Wasn't that the house
that woman passed away in?

37:15.767 --> 37:17.901
- No, I don't think so.

37:17.936 --> 37:20.970
- You remember,
that junkie girl, Rot Lady.

37:21.006 --> 37:23.573
- Her daughter explained
that she believed

37:23.608 --> 37:26.643
that the woman who lived
in the house before us

37:26.678 --> 37:29.746
<i>either committed suicide,</i>
<i>she overdosed.</i>

37:29.781 --> 37:32.449
- Me and Tarika saw them put
the body bag in the ambulance.

37:32.484 --> 37:35.485
¶ ¶

37:35.520 --> 37:37.620
- She ended up dying
in the house.

37:37.656 --> 37:39.422
¶ ¶

37:39.458 --> 37:40.957
- Bye.

37:40.992 --> 37:43.993
¶ ¶

37:44.029 --> 37:46.296
<i>- At that point we started</i>
<i>to research ways</i>

37:46.331 --> 37:47.931
that we could protect ourselves.

37:47.966 --> 37:50.633
¶ ¶

37:50.669 --> 37:54.938
- We read that if you put a
circle of salt around yourself,

37:54.973 --> 37:57.774
it offers some kind of
spiritual protection.

37:59.277 --> 38:01.845
<i>- We decided to move</i>
<i>our mattresses from our rooms</i>

38:01.880 --> 38:04.981
into the living room
so we can all sleep together

38:05.016 --> 38:07.383
to make sure that we're watching
each other's backs.

38:08.820 --> 38:12.255
<i>- We decided that we were gonna</i>
<i>make a big salt circle</i>

38:12.290 --> 38:13.790
around all of our mattresses.

38:15.494 --> 38:18.228
<i>We couldn't even</i>
<i>tell anybody about it.</i>

38:18.263 --> 38:19.696
We knew we would look crazy.

38:19.731 --> 38:21.431
No one would believe us.

38:21.466 --> 38:23.399
¶ ¶

38:25.103 --> 38:30.340
¶ ¶

38:30.375 --> 38:31.975
- The salt circle seemed
to work.

38:32.010 --> 38:37.146
¶ ¶

38:37.182 --> 38:40.950
There was no noises, no sounds.

38:40.986 --> 38:43.386
There was nothing.

38:43.421 --> 38:45.121
¶ ¶

38:45.156 --> 38:46.256
Graduation is there.

38:46.291 --> 38:49.192
It's right there.

38:49.227 --> 38:51.027
And we were all getting
more excited about it.

38:51.062 --> 38:53.229
Our projects were almost done.

38:53.265 --> 38:54.430
¶ ¶

38:54.466 --> 38:56.466
<i>After that week</i>
<i>we felt safe enough,</i>

38:56.501 --> 38:58.635
so we moved our beds
back into our rooms.

38:58.670 --> 39:01.538
[crickets chirping]

39:02.908 --> 39:10.847
¶ ¶

39:15.687 --> 39:22.625
¶ ¶

39:26.431 --> 39:28.865
[eerie whispering]

39:28.900 --> 39:30.833
[door creaking]

39:32.037 --> 39:32.969
<i>- I woke up.</i>

39:35.574 --> 39:37.407
It was, like, 1:00 a.m.

39:37.442 --> 39:40.376
[humming]

39:44.883 --> 39:48.051
¶ ¶

39:48.086 --> 39:50.286
The woman was at the base
of the bed.

39:50.322 --> 39:54.157
¶ ¶

39:54.192 --> 39:56.559
She was staring straight at me.

39:56.595 --> 39:58.361
¶ ¶

40:02.067 --> 40:05.835
<i>I put my hands on the bed.</i>

40:05.870 --> 40:08.204
There were sharp things
in my hands.

40:13.912 --> 40:15.545
- No, no!

40:15.580 --> 40:18.915
- I don't think I've ever been
that frightened in my life.

40:18.950 --> 40:21.584
- Please, help.

40:21.620 --> 40:22.785
No!

40:26.524 --> 40:29.459
[glass creaking]

40:31.997 --> 40:34.097
[screaming]

40:34.132 --> 40:36.966
- Lindsay? Lindsay?
- Kristin!

40:37.002 --> 40:38.034
Kristin, open the door!

40:38.069 --> 40:39.936
- Open the door.
- Kristin!

40:39.971 --> 40:41.738
- I can't open the door.

40:41.773 --> 40:44.140
- [screaming]

40:44.175 --> 40:46.009
- What's happening?
- Kristin!

40:46.044 --> 40:47.043
- And I am shoving

40:47.078 --> 40:48.645
<i>to get to Kristin.</i>

40:48.680 --> 40:50.213
- [screaming]

40:50.248 --> 40:51.681
Stop! Please!

40:51.716 --> 40:53.616
[evil shrieking]

40:53.652 --> 40:55.418
- [screaming]

40:55.453 --> 40:58.137
¶ ¶

41:02.361 --> 41:03.460
¶ ¶

41:03.495 --> 41:06.363
-<i> [crying]</i>

41:06.398 --> 41:09.233
[screaming]

41:09.268 --> 41:11.635
Stop, please!

41:11.670 --> 41:13.270
[evil shrieking]

41:13.305 --> 41:15.172
[thudding]

41:15.207 --> 41:16.573
- We're trying to get
the door open,

41:16.609 --> 41:18.675
but we just can't get it.

41:18.711 --> 41:19.943
- Oh, my God!
What is happening?

41:19.979 --> 41:22.045
- And Kristin's just screaming
her head off.

41:22.081 --> 41:23.046
[glass shatters]

41:23.082 --> 41:24.681
- Oh, my God.
What happened?

41:24.717 --> 41:27.217
- And Kristin's covered
in blood.

41:27.253 --> 41:29.753
- Where is the first aid kit?
- Oh, God.

41:29.788 --> 41:32.689
- The mirror was just shattered,
and glass was all in her bed.

41:32.725 --> 41:33.957
¶ ¶

41:33.993 --> 41:37.194
- I just had blood
all over my shirt and my arms.

41:37.229 --> 41:39.630
- It's okay, it's okay,
it's okay, it's okay.

41:39.665 --> 41:42.199
- There was three slash marks
across my stomach,

41:42.234 --> 41:45.769
three slash marks
across my chest.

41:45.804 --> 41:48.038
- We're gonna leave right now.
We're gonna leave tonight.

41:48.073 --> 41:49.306
<i>- I was like,</i>
<i>"We need to get out.</i>

41:49.341 --> 41:50.941
We need to go."

41:50.976 --> 41:52.242
- Let's go, let's go.
- Come on.

41:52.278 --> 41:54.444
- Oh, my God.
- Hurry, hurry.

41:54.480 --> 41:56.947
- Here, it's okay, it's okay.

41:56.982 --> 41:58.749
- Go, get in, get in.

41:58.784 --> 42:00.250
¶ ¶

42:00.286 --> 42:02.352
- Hurry.
- It hurts.

42:02.388 --> 42:07.324
¶ ¶

42:23.709 --> 42:26.276
<i>- It's my</i>
<i>first job interview today.</i>

42:26.312 --> 42:27.344
<i>Can I show you guys</i>
<i>some dresses?</i>

42:27.379 --> 42:28.612
<i>- Oh, okay.</i>

42:28.647 --> 42:31.348
- I feel that nobody
outside of the three of us

42:31.383 --> 42:34.785
will ever understand what
we went through in that house.

42:34.820 --> 42:36.119
<i>Everything that happened</i>

42:36.155 --> 42:38.755
<i>I think just brought us</i>
<i>closer together.</i>

42:38.791 --> 42:41.191
We've lived apart
for almost a year now,

42:41.226 --> 42:43.126
and we're still
as close as ever.

42:46.265 --> 42:54.204
¶ ¶
